==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: deprecatory
<hw>dep"re*ca*to*ry</hw>
<pr>(d⟦ecr⟧p"r⟦esl⟧*k⟦adot⟧*t⟦osl⟧*r⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>deprecatorius</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Tending to remove or
avert evil by prayer; apologetic.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Humble and <qex>deprecatory</qex> letters.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Serving to deprecate; expressing a low opinion
of.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> belittling, disparaging, depreciative, deprecatory,
depreciatory, derogatory, detractive, detracting, slighting, pejorative,
denigratory.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Depreciate</ent>⟦br⟧
